International Brief -- ABN Amro Bank N.V.:
   Hoare Govett to Be Bought
   From Security Pacific Corp.
For ABN Amro, the deal is part of a strategy of
European-wide expansion. The purchase is expected to be made
formal in the second quarter. ABN Amro was created two years
ago by the merger of two Dutch banks, Algemene Bank Nederland
and Amsterdam Rotterdam Bank.
   Separately, Dutch insurance group Aegon N.V. said it holds
a 12.84% stake in ABN Amro. Under a new Dutch law, holders
must disclose stakes of more than 5% in publicly traded
companies.